tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  99,3,"(And man) i.e. the disbeliever (saith: What aileth her?) He says this in astonishment from the horror he sees"
  99,5,"(Because thy Lord inspires her) because your Lord gives her leave to talk."
  99,8,"(And whoso doeth ill an atom's weight) the weight of a small atom (will see it then) is written in his register and will displease him; and it is also said: the believer sees it in the life of the world while the disbeliever sees it in the Hereafter'."
  100,7,"(And lo! he is a witness unto that) and Allah records His doing;"
  100,8,"(And lo! in the love of wealth) abundant wealth (he) i.e. Qurt (is violent) is extreme."